main event: A brilliant round, white object was observed in Lincoln, Nebraska, that seemed to hover and fade out instantaneously.
interesting points: The object was somewhat smaller than a full moon., The sighting lasted approximately 1-2 minutes., The object was observed at a 65-degree elevation from the observer's position., The observer was a reliable rated Air Force navigator., The preparing officer believes the object sighted was likely a meteor.
witness description: Captain E. Graybill, reliable Air Force navigator
